17 double MotorEfficiency::calculate(double loadFactor, double specifiedEfficiency) {
18  if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::SPECIFIED && specifiedEfficiency < 0) {
19  throw std::runtime_error("An efficiency must be specified if EfficiencyClass::SPECIFIED is used");
20  }
21 
22  std::array<double, 5> motorEfficiency = {};
23  if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::ENERGY_EFFICIENT
24  || efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::STANDARD
25  || efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::PREMIUM)
26  {
27  motorEfficiency = MotorEfficiency(lineFrequency, motorRpm, efficiencyClass, motorRatedPower).calculate25intervals();
28  } else if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::SPECIFIED) {
29  // For specified efficiency, you have to first choose the nominal efficiency.
30  motorEfficiency = MotorEfficiency(lineFrequency, motorRpm, Motor::EfficiencyClass::ENERGY_EFFICIENT,
31  motorRatedPower).calculate25intervals();
32  auto const stdMotorEffs = MotorEfficiency(lineFrequency, motorRpm, Motor::EfficiencyClass::STANDARD, motorRatedPower).calculate25intervals();
33 
34 // double C = specifiedEfficiency / motorEfficiency[3];
35  if (std::fabs(motorEfficiency[3] - specifiedEfficiency) > std::fabs(stdMotorEffs[3] - specifiedEfficiency)) {
36  //SE chosen
37  const double C = specifiedEfficiency / stdMotorEffs[3];
38  motorEfficiency = {
39  {
40  stdMotorEffs[0] * C, stdMotorEffs[1] * C, stdMotorEffs[2] * C,
41  stdMotorEffs[4] * C, stdMotorEffs[4] * C
42  }
43  };
44  } else { // EE chosen
45  specifiedEfficiency = specifiedEfficiency / 100;
46  const double C = specifiedEfficiency / motorEfficiency[3];
47 
48  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < 5; ++i) {
49  motorEfficiency[i] = motorEfficiency[i] * C;
50  }
51  }
52  }
53 
72  const double kWloss25 = ((1 / motorEfficiency[0]) - 1) * motorRatedPower * 0.746 * 0.25;
73  kWloss0 = 0.8 * kWloss25;
74 
75  if (loadFactor < 0.251) {
76  // loadFactor <= 0.25
77  const double kWloss = kWloss0 + loadFactor * 100 * (kWloss25 - kWloss0) / 25;
78  const double kWshaft = motorRatedPower * 0.746 * (loadFactor); // Make sure motorRatedPower is in hp
79  const double kWe = kWloss + kWshaft; // Input electric power
80  motorEff = kWshaft / kWe; //Final efficiency calculation
81  } else if (loadFactor < 1.251) {
89  CurveFitVal cfv({.25, .50, .75, 1.00, 1.25}, {motorEfficiency[0], motorEfficiency[1], motorEfficiency[2], motorEfficiency[3], motorEfficiency[4]}, 4, loadFactor);
90  motorEff = cfv.calculate();
91  } else {
97  if (loadFactor > 1.5) {
98  loadFactor = 1.5;
99  }
100  CurveFitVal cfv({.75, 1.00, 1.25}, {motorEfficiency[2], motorEfficiency[3], motorEfficiency[4]}, 2, loadFactor);
101  motorEff = cfv.calculate();
102  }
103 
104  return motorEff;
105 }

454 std::array<double, 5> MotorEfficiency::calculate25intervals() {
455  // Find the poles and use it as an index
456  int poleCase = Poles(motorRpm, lineFrequency).calculate() / 2 - 1;
457  if (efficiencyClass == Motor::EfficiencyClass::PREMIUM && poleCase > 2) {
458  poleCase = 2;
459  }
460  auto const plCoeffs = determinePartialLoadCoefficients(static_cast<std::size_t>(poleCase));
461 
462  auto const effCalc = [this, &plCoeffs] (std::size_t const i) {
463  return (plCoeffs[0][i] + (plCoeffs[1][i] * std::exp(-plCoeffs[2][i] * motorRatedPower)) +
464  (plCoeffs[3][i] * std::exp(-plCoeffs[4][i] * motorRatedPower))) / 100;
465  };
466 
474  return {{effCalc(0), effCalc(1), effCalc(2), effCalc(3), 0.99 * effCalc(3)}};
475 }
